claim.claim-text:
A device (74) for forming the ends of a pipe element, the device (74) comprising a first roller (78) and second roller (80) for imparting a shape to a sidewall of a pipe element, wherein said first roller (78) rotates about an axis (82) and comprises:
• a first segment (94) having a first outer diameter (94a);
• a second segment (96) positioned contiguous with said first segment (94) and having a second outer diameter (96a) smaller than said first outer diameter (94a);
• a third segment (98) positioned contiguous with said second segment (96) and having a third outer diameter (98a) larger than said second outer diameter (96a);
and wherein said second roller (80) rotates about an axis (88) and comprises:
• a fourth segment (104) having a fourth outer diameter (104a);
• a fifth segment (106) positioned contiguous with said fourth segment (104) and having a fifth outer diameter (106a) greater than said fourth outer diameter (104a);
• a sixth segment (108) positioned contiguous with said fifth segment (106) and having an sixth outer diameter (108a) less than said fifth outer diameter (106a); and
• a seventh segment (110) positioned contiguous with said sixth segment (108) and having a seventh outer diameter (110a) approximately equal to said fifth outer diameter (106a).

The device according to Claim 1, wherein said fifth segment (106) comprises:
• a first annular surface (114) positioned adjacent to said fourth segment (104);
• a second annular surface (116) positioned adjacent to said sixth segment (108) and oriented angularly with respect to said second axis (88).

The device according to Claim 2, said device further comprising:
• a support frame (76);
• said first roller (78) being mounted on said support frame (76) and being rotatable about a first axis (82), said first roller (78) being adapted to engage an inner surface of said pipe element;
• Means (90) for rotating said first roller (78) about said first axis (82);
• said second roller (80) being mounted on said support frame (76) and being rotatable about a second axis (88) oriented substantially parallel to said first axis (82), said second roller (80) being movable toward and away from said first roller (78) and being adapted to engage an outer surface of said pipe element;
• means (90) for moving said second roller (80) relatively to said first roller (78) for compressing said sidewall there between while said rollers rotate, said rollers being arranged relatively to one another on said support frame (76) such that:
• said fourth segment (104) is aligned with said first segment (94);
• said fifth segment (106) is aligned with said second segment (96);
• said sixth segment (108) is aligned with said third segment (98); and
• said seventh segment (110) is aligned with said eighth segment (100) and at least a portion of said ninth segment (102).

A method of imparting said shape to said sidewall of said pipe element having an inner surface and an outer surface by using the device of first and second rollers according to Claims 1-9, said method comprising:
• contacting said inner surface at a first point on said first segment of said first roller;
• contacting said outer surface at a third point on said fifth segment of said second roller;
• rotating one of said first and second rollers thereby causing the other of said first and second rollers and said pipe element to rotate, said first roller circumferentially traversing said inner surface, said second roller circumferentially traversing said outer surface;
• moving one of said first and second rollers toward the other of said first and second rollers and deforming said sidewall of said pipe element through contact between said inner surface and said first and third segments of said first roller and contact between said outer surface and said fifth and seventh segments of said second roller;
• continue moving one of said first and second rollers toward the other of said first and second rollers and compressing said sidewall of said pipe element between said first segment of said first roller and said fourth segment of said second roller;
• continue moving one of said first and second rollers toward the other of said first and second rollers and compressing said sidewall of said pipe element between said second segment of said first roller and said fifth segment of said second roller;
• continue moving one of said first and second rollers toward the other of said first and second rollers and compressing said sidewall of said pipe element between said third segment of said first roller and said fifth and seventh segments of said second roller.
